                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Colombia/45: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Keith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-30T23:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 30, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 31—3:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>429. With reference to my telegram no. 414 March 25, 11 p.m. This afternoon when
                    seeing the President<note n="54" xml:id="d200fn54">Eduardo Santos.</note> I
                    referred to the note submitted the Foreign Office on rubber emphasizing its
                    urgency and importance. The President stated he would study the matter carefully
                    this week and I would have some response by April 8. He added, “You can count on
                    my aid.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Keith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
